It was assumed Xi (.) and Uij (.) were uncorrelated with E (Xi (v))=μx (v) and E (Uij (v))=0, therefore, the Best Linear Unbiased Estimator (BLUE) of Xi (v) was defined as Equation (9) (Shou et al., 2014):
(9) V^i2SH(v)=Xi^(v)=λ(v)*V^2M(v)+{1−λ(v)}*V^i2R(v) , where:
(10) λ(v)=Var{Xi(v)}Var{Xi(v)}+Var{Ui1(v)}
